<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8290] Streams Not Closing Fenced Producer On Task Close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8290</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a producer is fenced during processing a rebalance is triggered and Kafka Streams closes the (zombie) task, but not the producer.&#160; When EOS is enabled and we close a task the producer should always be closed regardless if it was fenced or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
